# `fn main()` (no parameters) is one of two accepted main signatures.
# The codegen wrapper for a void main returns 0 unconditionally.
#
# Kept separate from main_wrapper_valid because MIR permits only one
# `fn main` per file — a second declaration fires TC-DuplicateDeclaration
# and would mask the signature check under test here.
fn main() {
  entry:
    return
}
